text: Esenbeckia alata is a species of flowering plant in the citrus family, Rutaceae, that is endemic to Colombia. Common names include Winged Esenbeckia, Coya, and Cuala-cuala. ==References== alata Category:Endemic flora of Colombia Category:Plants described in 1872 Category:Endangered plants Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot
